				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The "color clock" is the period of the NTSC color subcarrier, or 3.5795&#773;4&#773; MHz.
<br />
<br />CCIR specifies that the NTSC picture area is 176 color clocks wide by 240 pixels tall. Now, one CPU clock = 2 NTSC color clocks = 3 pixels, so 176 color clocks is 264 NES pixels. The picture area of a field is still 240 lines tall, so the area that you have to stretch to 4:3 is 264x240.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

